Warzones represent a tug of war mechanic, with a Control value. When at 0 or less Control, they roll dice that might poison the player's deck with temporary curse cards. When at positive control, they roll dice that might put some nice cards in the player's deck. On average, it is worse to have a location in a negative control state than it is good to have a location in a positive control state.

When a location becomes positive for the first time, a Person of Interest is revealed. A PoI has two Influence thresholds that can be hit; the first threshold will reward the player with a consumable or perhaps a relic. The second threshold will reward the player with the PoI itself, as a special permanent card in the player's deck that is very good.

If a location goes to 0 or below while a PoI is revealed, that PoI becomes hostile and becomes a permanent curse in the deck for the rest of the run.


